&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 4 Therapy Assistant Practitioner: 6 months Stroke Review and rehabilitation&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in working as part of a friendly, well-established community rehabilitation team, supporting therapy services to adults with predominantly neurological disorders within the community?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Lewisham Adult Therapy Team has a vacancy for a Band 4 Therapy Assistant Practitioner who would like to develop their skills in the field of adult neurology, specifically stroke. You would be part of a supportive multidisciplinary rehabilitation team joining physiotherapists, occupational therapists, speech and language therapists, and rehabilitation assistants.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You would be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Carrying out the 6 month post-stroke review for Lewisham registered patients. The purpose of this service is to offer a review of the health and social care needs of individuals who are living in the Borough of Lewisham, at approximately 6 months after having a stroke. This role works as part of the stroke pathway team and the review is seen as a vital part of the patient’s journey. The role includes collecting and inputting information into the SSNAP database and requires good administration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working under the supervision of qualified therapy staff (speech and language therapy, physiotherapy, and occupational therapy), in providing assessment, rehabilitation, management, and discharge of patients in a community setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an individual with excellent communication skills and good organisational skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameGeraldine DakinJob titleLead Speech and Language TherapistEmail addressgeraldine.dakin@nhs.netTelephone number0203 049 4492Additional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Geraldine Dakin, Clinical Lead Speech and Language Therapist on geraldine.dakin@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
